result.execSummary:
The defendant Edward J Rosebrook was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Edward J Rosebrook is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Edward J Rosebrook was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Defendant Edward J Rosebrook in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that the matter is resolved.  Atty Hendee moves to amend Ct. 1 to Poss of THC without the repeater.    Atty Hendee states plea agreement to the amended Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.  Atty Gumz agrees.  Defendant agrees.
BY THE COURT:  Ct. 1 amended to remove the repeater.

Court questions the defendant.  Defendant enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of the amended Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

Atty Gumz makes sentencing arguments.

BY THE COURT:  Amended Ct. 1:  Withhold Sentence; 12 months Probation with conditions:
10 days in the Marquette County Jail w/huber
  Report on or before December 2, 2016 by 7:00pm, clean & sober.
Court Costs = $243.00
  DNA Sample + $200.00 Surcharge
Comply with any and all counseling recommended by the Agent
Defendant is to pay while on probation
Ct. 2 to be dismissed.
Plea/sentencing hearing on November 2, 2016 at 01:15 pm.
